content.description: Climb the right side of the cave feature, out a bulge, then up a friendly slab to the anchors.
content.location: It is on the right side of the cave feature towards the left end of the wall.

content.description: Climb a short pillar feature, then go up to the third bolt where the crux moves up and left are encountered. Continue up on slabby terrain to the anchors.
content.location: It is in the middle of the crag. See the photo.

climbs.name: Nova
climbs.fa: J. Tarry, C. Hofer, B. Scott

content.description: Climb the arch feature to a cruxy bulge, then continue on continuous, tricky face to the anchors. This is a good route!
content.location: It is mid-crag above an inset arch.

content.description: Climb the crux slab getting off the ground, then go up easy terrain to the crack. Follow it to the anchors.
content.location: This is the rightmost route on the crag.

content.description: Climb a right-facing, right-angling dihedral past somewhat powerful and tricky climbing to anchors.
content.location: This is the leftmost route at the crag.

content.description: Climb 5.easy up to 4 bolts of small holds. This is fingery and pumpy with a tricky clip.

Intergalactic has fun, techy, and sequential climbing.

Climb easy terrain to the scoop. From here, continuous sequential climbing leads to the anchor.
content.location: Begin below the big scoop towards the right side of the crag. See the photo.

content.description: Start just right of a small tree, and climb blocky terrain to underclings that reach a roof. Climb the crux roof and techy terrain to the anchors. The rock around the roof is so-so, but the movement is great.
content.location: This is on the right third of the cliff under the high, blocky roof.

content.description:
Black Hole has thin, continuous face climbing.

Climb the left side of the cave feature then up on sustained difficult face climbing to the anchors.
content.location: This is on the left side of the cave feature at the left end of the crag.

content.description:
Blast off at the crux then hang on for the ride to the top. Unfortunately the crux is exponentially harder if you are short.

Climb up to the roof, and figure out how to get into the undercling, then launch for the rounded arete feature. Continue past a tricky move into the V groove, then easier climbing leads to anchors shared with

Oh' Ryan

.
content.location:
It is mid-crag between

Oh' Ryan

and

Andromeda Galaxy

. See the photo.

climbs.name: Andromeda Galaxy
climbs.fa: J. Tarry, C. Hofer, B. Scott

content.description: Climb up past a high third bolt and diagonal left (tricky if you are short). Continue up to crux moves moving right midway up the climb then up to the anchors.
content.location: This ascends somewhat broken rock towards the mid-right side of the crag. See the photo.
